The paper proposes a deep neural network for action recognition in videos, which involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of attention regularization, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also evaluates its model on two video datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
